  WEBB SIMPSON:   It was just a perfect 9‑iron, held it up against a little bit of wind, and it came off perfect.   I loved it.   It gave us an opportunity to close it out.  
   
 Q.   You guys had some chances early and let them slip away.   Any time on the back nine you felt like you were making a run?   
BUBBA WATSON:   You know, we never really‑‑ we just kept missing putts.   We could never get any momentum going our way.   They were holing putts, they were playing great golf, and they just beat us.   
   
  
  
  
  
  

